<h2>School Policies</h2>

<div class="policies-container">
  <!-- Warning Message -->
  <div class="warning-message">
    <p>
      <strong>Warning:</strong> Failure to adhere to these rules will result in
      strict action being taken against the violators. We expect all students to
      follow the school's code of conduct diligently.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>1. Code of Conduct</h3>
    <p>
      All students are expected to adhere to a high standard of behavior.
      Respect towards teachers, staff, and fellow students is mandatory at all
      times.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>2. Attendance Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Regular attendance is crucial for academic success. Students must attend
      all classes unless there are valid reasons, and parents must notify the
      school of any absences.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>3. Dress Code</h3>
    <p>
      Students are required to wear the school uniform during school hours. The
      uniform promotes a sense of unity and pride in our school community.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>4. Bullying Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Bullying in any form is strictly prohibited. The school promotes a safe
      and inclusive environment, and any instances of bullying will be addressed
      promptly.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>5. Homework Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Homework is an essential part of the learning process. Students are
      expected to complete assignments on time, and parents are encouraged to
      support their children in this process.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>6. Safety and Security Policy</h3>
    <p>
      The safety and security of our students is a top priority. All students
      must comply with safety regulations, including evacuation procedures and
      emergency drills.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>7. Technology Use Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Students are expected to use school technology responsibly. Any misuse of
      devices or software will result in disciplinary action, including
      potential loss of technology privileges.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>8. Respect and Diversity Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Our school promotes an inclusive environment that respects diversity.
      Discrimination or harassment of any kind is not tolerated and will be
      addressed immediately.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>9. Parent Involvement Policy</h3>
    <p>
      We encourage parents to be actively involved in their children's
      education. Regular communication between the school and home is essential
      for student success.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>10. Substance Abuse Policy</h3>
    <p>
      The use of drugs and alcohol is strictly prohibited on school premises.
      Students found in violation of this policy will face severe disciplinary
      actions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>11. Field Trip Policy</h3>
    <p>
      All students participating in field trips must have parental permission.
      Students are expected to adhere to school behavior standards during these
      events.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy">
    <h3>12. Grievance Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Students and parents are encouraged to voice concerns regarding school
      policies or issues. A clear grievance procedure is in place to address
      these matters effectively.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
